# Form section structure and spacing

Use a two-level pattern for tool forms:

1. Top-level section stack uses `.form-body`
2. Each individual section uses `.form-section`

## Spacing intent

- `.form-body` controls spacing **between sections** (larger rhythm, currently 24px).
- `.form-section` controls spacing **inside a section** (tighter label/control spacing, currently 12px).

Do **not** use `.form-section` as both the outer stack and inner section wrapper on the same form area.

## Recommended markup pattern

```html
<div class="form-body">
  <div class="form-section">
    <!-- label + control(s) -->
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <!-- next section -->
  </div>
</div>
```

## Why

This keeps vertical rhythm predictable:

- tighter spacing within each control group
- consistent larger spacing between distinct groups
